        {
            "title": "BRC Group Holdings (RILY) surged 38.53% in after-hours trading to $10.44 on Q3 report, net income $89.1M, revenue $277.9M.",
            "id": "df4dd2bf-6660-4ab7-8bb9-44a20f2207ef",
            "description": "After-hours trading on Wednesday saw BRC Group Holdings Inc. (NASDAQ: RILY) shares surge by 38.53% to $10.44, following the release of their Q3 earnings report and regulatory filing. The California-based company reported a significant improvement in financials, with a net income of $89.1 million for the quarter ended Sept. 30, 2025, a notable increase from the $286.4 million net loss in the same period the previous year. Diluted earnings per share also saw a positive turn, standing at $2.91 in Q3 2025 compared to a loss of $9.39 per share in Q3 2024. Total revenues for the quarter amounted to $277.9 million, showcasing a growth from $175.4 million year-over-year. The Capital Markets segment of the company reported an income of $60.7 million during this period. For more details, the complete report is available on Benzinga.com.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/df4dd2bf-6660-4ab7-8bb9-44a20f2207ef",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-15 14:21:06",
            "source": "unusualwhales",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        }
